history.content: Drop 188 (this cancels the existing swap) and enroll in 170 as a swap option for 184. As with swaps, its not guaranteed how the system will handle it but this should be your best bet.

During Phase 1 enrollment, I enrolled in CS 188 with a swap for CS 184. Now that CS 170 is open, I'd like to modify my swap such that 170 swaps with 184 without losing my spot on the 184 waitlist. Is something like this possible?

I imagine I could drop 188 without dropping 184, add 170, and create a swap between 170 and 184, but I'm unsure of whether this would work. I've already looked into @10114, but wasn't sure how it might apply to this case (changing out the class from which one swaps away). Many thanks!
history.subject: Modifying a Swap
